{"title_page": "Mikhail Khabarov", "text_new": "{{short description|Russian businessman}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Mikhail Kharabov\n| birth_date         = March 12, 1971\n| birth_place        = [[Zlatoust]], [[Chelyabinsk]], [[USSR]]\n| nationality        = {{flagicon|RUS}} Russian\n| occupation         = Businessman, Manager\n}}\n'''Mikhail Valentinovich Khabarov''' (born in March 12, 1971, in [[Zlatoust]], [[Chelyabinsk]], [[Soviet Union|USSR]]) is a [[Russia|Russian]] businessman and manager. He is the current board president, and [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] of National Bank TRUST<ref name=\"trust\">{{cite web|url=https://www.trust.ru/upload/documents/about/leaders/government_body_02122019.pdf|title=\u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0431\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430 \u0422\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0442|website=Trust|accessdate=2019-12-02}}</ref>, an institution part of the [[Central Bank of Russia]]'s activities to improve the national banking system.\n\n== Biography ==\n\n=== Early life ===\nMikhail Khabarov was born in Zlatoust, Chelyabinsk, USSR, in a family of [[Metallurgy|metallurgists]]. His parents wanted that his son continued the family's business, but Khaborov didn't settle as the material life of his parents didn't impress him. In his first opportunity, he left his hometown for [[Moscow]].<ref name=\"forbes\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.ru/forbes/issue/2007-03/12083-ohotnik-za-millionerami|title=\u041e\u0445\u043e\u0442\u043d\u0438\u043a \u0437\u0430 \u043c\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043c\u0438|website=Forbes|accessdate=2020-02-26}}</ref>\n\n=== Education ===\nMikhail Khabarov joined the Moscow Institute of Steel and Alloys State Technological University (currently known as [[National University of Science and Technology MISiS (Russia)|National University of Science and Technology MISiS]]). He graduated in 1993 in Automation of Technological Processes and Metallurgical Production.<ref name=\"forbes\" /><ref name=\"finparty\">{{cite web|url=https://finparty.ru/personal/mikhail-khabarov/|title=\u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432|website=Finparty|accessdate=2020-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/1227444|title=8 \u043e\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430|date=2009-09-07|publisher=www.kommersant.ru|lang=ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref> In 1994, he concluded his studies in the Higher Commercial School, under the Russian Federation's [[Ministry of Foreign Economic Relations (Soviet Union)|Ministry of Foreign Economic Relations]]. In 2001, he received his MBA from [[Pepperdine University]]  ([[California]], [[United States|USA]]).<ref name=\"finparty\" /> Speculation in Russia suggested that the true motive of his departure from Russia to USA in the Fall of 1998, was a criminal prosecution from various of the most important managers of the financial and industrial group [[Magnitogorsk Iron and Steel Works]]. Khabarov was accused of [[embezzlement]] of a 30% stake in Magnitogorsk Iron and Steel Works, and asset withdrawal.<ref name=\"skelet\">{{Cite web|url=https://finance.rambler.ru/other/43424867-skelet-v-shkafu-seo-trasta-mihaila-habarova/|title=\u0421\u043a\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0442 \u0432 \u0448\u043a\u0430\u0444\u0443 \u0421\u0415\u041e \u00ab\u0422\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0430\u00bb \u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430|publisher=\u0420\u0430\u043c\u0431\u043b\u0435\u0440/\u0444\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043d\u0441\u044b|lang=ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nMikhael Khabarov started his career as a window cleaner, and worked as an ice cream salesman.<ref name=\"snob\">{{cite web|url=https://snob.ru/profile/5282|title=\u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432|website=\u0421\u043d\u043e\u0431|accessdate=2020-02-26}}</ref> In 1993-1994, he was employed at the Department of Automation in the Ministry of Metallurgy of Russian Federadion. In an interview some years later, Khabarov recalled that, when applying for the job, the interviewer made the following note on his resume: \u201cHe has zero knowledge in finance, but he understands metallurgy,\u201d and that he was then appointed on probation in the bank\u2019s corporate finance department<ref name=\"snob\" /> \n\n=== Inkombank and Magnitogorsk Steel ===\nIn 1994, he was hired by [[Inkombank]] as manager-in-chief. In 1996, Khabarov moved to the office of Deputy Director of Economy, Finance, and Strategical Development in the financial and industrial group Magnitogorsk Steel, that along with Inkombank and FIG, held Magnitogorsk Iron and Steel Works (MMK).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/182026|title=Trans World \u0438 \u0418\u043d\u043a\u043e\u043c\u0431\u0430\u043d\u043a \u043d\u0430 \u041c\u0430\u0433\u043d\u0438\u0442\u043a\u0435|date=1997-08-05|publisher=www.kommersant.ru|lang=ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref> Khabarov worked in the team under Rashit Sharipov, Chairman of the Board of Directors of the Magnitogorsk Iron and Steel works. In the same year, e and his wife and son moved to the United States, and moved back to Russia after the statute of limitations for the criminal cases related to the Magnitogorsk Iron and Steel Works had expired.<ref name=\"skelet\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vekdaily.com/economy/skeleton-in-the-closet-of-trust-bank-ceo-mikhail-khabarov|title=Skeleton in the Closet of Trust Bank CEO Mikhail Khabarov|website=Vekdaily.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n=== ROSNO Asset Management Alliance ===\nBack to Russia, Mikhail Khabarov was hired by the Finance Director of the Insurance Company [[ROSNO]]. In 2004, Khabarov created and presided over ROSNO Asset Management Alliance. According to Forbes, in the exact period, the co-owner of [[Alfa Group|Alfa Capital]]<ref name=\"forbes\" />, [[Mikhail Fridman]] was looking for a CEO. In May 2006, Khabarov left ROSNO with a group of specialists to Alfa Capital.<ref name=\"famp\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.ru/amp/376323/|title=\u0421\u043f\u0435\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0441\u0442 \u043f\u043e \u043f\u043b\u043e\u0445\u0438\u043c \u0434\u043e\u043b\u0433\u0430\u043c. CEO \u0431\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430 \u00ab\u0422\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0442\u00bb \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b \u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432 {{!}} Forbes.ru|publisher=www.forbes.ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref>\n\n=== Alfa Group ===\nIn October 2010, he became president of the investments company A1 ([[Alfa Group]]'s division of investments), while remaining Chairman of the Board of Directors at Alfa Capital. At the same time, he joined Supervisory Board of Alfa Group.<ref name=\"finparty\" /> Under Khabarov, A1 managed the Alfa Distressed Assets Fund (ADA), which redeemed troubled collateral assets from Alfa Group, and made them operational again before selling them on. In this process, nearly US$2 billions of toxic assets were brought under the control of A1.<ref name=\"famp\" /> \n\nKhabarov conducted A1 to become one of the most aggressive players in the market of hostile takeovers and applying all sorts of raider tools from quasi-legal methods to more primitive forms of exerting pressure, including initiating criminal cases against intractable opponents.<ref>http://www.ng.ru/economics/2020-01-30/100_trast300120.html</ref> Indeed, media reported on some of the most controversial cases in which A1 was involved, including the liquidation of the budget airline [[Avianova (Russia)|Avianova]], the interception of liquid assets of Russia\u2019s largest ceramic tile producer Stroyfarfor, the illegal takeover and its alleged manipulation of US and EU sanctions against defense enterprises [[Rostec]] and [[Uralvagonzavod]], among others.<ref name=\"versia\">{{Cite web|url=https://versia.ru/ploximi-dolgami-v-gosbanke-trast-zanimaetsya-byvshij-direktor-a1-mixail-xabarov|title=\u041f\u043b\u043e\u0445\u0438\u043c\u0438 \u0434\u043e\u043b\u0433\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u0432 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0431\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0435 \u00ab\u0422\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0442\u00bb \u0437\u0430\u043d\u0438\u043c\u0430\u0435\u0442\u0441\u044f \u0431\u044b\u0432\u0448\u0438\u0439 \u0434\u0438\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u04101 \u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432|publisher=versia.ru|lang=ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref>  \n\nKhabarov's management of A1 lasted until December 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vedomosti.ru/newspaper/articles/2015/02/26/habarov-vzyalsya-za-furi|title=\u0411\u044b\u0432\u0448\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u04101 \u0437\u0430\u0439\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0441\u044f \u0444\u0443\u0440\u0430\u043c\u0438|publisher=\u0412\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438|lang=ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref> By the time Mikhail Khabarov was named for the National Trust Bank, in 2019, media called Khabarov \"something between a racketeer and a collector\".<ref name=\"versia\" /> Since 2014, Khabarov has been co-owner and president of the logistics company Delovie Linii.<ref name=\"snob\" /> \n\n=== National Bank TRUST ===\nIn May 2019, he was named Prime First Deputy President-Chairman of the Management Board and Chief Executive Officer of the National Bank TRUST Non-core Assets.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://worldfinancialreview.com/mikhail-khabarov-of-a1-now-heads-national-bank-trust/|title=Mikhail Khabarov of A1 Now Heads National Bank TRUST|last=|first=|date=|website=World Financial Review|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The bank was created to consolidate bad assets from an extensive clean-up of various financial institutions including [[Otkritie FC Bank|Otkrytie FC]], [[B&N Bank]] , [[Promsvyazbank]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-russia-banks-bad-bank-exclusive-idUSKCN1Q10MH|title=Exclusive: Russia expects to recover far less from 'bad bank' assets - sources|date=2019-02-12|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-03-12|language=en}}</ref>. Khabarov is responsible for the issues related to money charges: administration and sales of assets, and debt collection.<ref name=\"famp\" /> The amount of problematic assets consolidated in the bank amounts to 450 billion rubles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/3975307|title=\u0413\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u044b\u043c \u0438\u0441\u043f\u043e\u043b\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u043c \u0434\u0438\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043c \u0411\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430 \u043d\u0435\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043e\u0432 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b \u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432|date=2019-05-20|publisher=www.kommersant.ru|lang=ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref> The president of the bank's council, Alexander Sokolov, by the time of Khabarov's appointment, appointed him as \"a professional with good experience in the management of problematic assets\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.finmarket.ru/interview/Default.asp?id=5017787|title=\u0412\u0440\u0435\u043c\u044f \u0432\u0441\u0435\u0433\u0434\u0430 \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u043a\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0430 - \u0433\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0430 \u0431\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430 &quot;\u0422\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0442&quot;|date=2019-06-11|publisher=Finmarket.ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref> At the same time, media observed that Khabarov was recruiting former employees from A1, with dubious reputations to work with National Bank TRUST.<ref name=\"versia\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pravda.ru/society/1467649-Mikhail_Khabarov/|title=\u041c\u0435\u0442\u043e\u0434\u044b \u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0431\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0437\u0430\u043c\u0433\u043b\u0430\u0432\u044b \u0431\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430 \"\u0422\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0442\" \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430|author=\u041f\u0435\u0442\u0440 \u0414\u0435\u0440\u044f\u0431\u0438\u043d|date=2020-01-17|publisher=\u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0434\u0430.\u0420\u0443|lang=ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://oneworldherald.com/2020/01/05/national-bank-trust-executive-director-mikhail-khabarov-goes-big/|title=National bank Trust executive director Mikhail Khabarov goes big|last=heraldadmin|date=2020-01-05|website=OneWorldHerald.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n== Conflict within Delovie Linii ==\nIn 2015, Khabarov became co-owner of one of the largest logistics companies in Russia - Delovie Linii. In August 2017, Khabarov had a conflict with other co-owner Alexander Bogatikov. In September 2019, Solarstones Limited, a company from [[Seychelles]], controlled by Khabarov, installed a lawsuit of US$ 25 million against Bogatikov and his company DL Management Limited, in the [[London Court of International Arbitration]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.ru/biznes/386747-sud-zapretil-vladelcam-delovyh-liniy-prodavat-svoi-aktivy|title=\u0421\u0443\u0434 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043b \u0432\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0446\u0430\u043c \u00ab\u0414\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445 \u043b\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0439\u00bb \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0438 \u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u044b {{!}} \u0411\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441|date=2019-11-05|publisher=Forbes.ru|lang=en-US|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref> Following a lawsuit filed by Solarstones Limited, the [[Primorsky District, Arkhangelsk Oblast|Primorsky]] District Court of [[Saint Petersburg|St. Petersburg]] prohibited any transactions for eight companies included in the Delovie Linii group, and inspectorate No. 15 of the Federal Tax Service for St. Petersburg registered such transactions as subjects of injunctive relief on 18 October 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sobesednik.ru/obshchestvo/20191205-femida-na-sluzhbe-u-ofshora|title=\u0424\u0435\u043c\u0438\u0434\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0435 \u0443 \u043e\u0444\u0448\u043e\u0440\u0430|publisher=sobesednik.ru|lang=ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.ru/biznes/386747-sud-zapretil-vladelcam-delovyh-liniy-prodavat-svoi-aktivy|title=\u0421\u0443\u0434 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043b \u0432\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0446\u0430\u043c \u00ab\u0414\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445 \u043b\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0439\u00bb \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0438 \u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u044b {{!}} \u0411\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441|date=2019-11-05|website=Forbes.ru|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\nAccording to media reports, these injunctions represent the next stage of a raid on the Delovie Linii, with judge Natalya Karpenkova, who was disciplined for \u201cgross and systematic violation of the procedural legislation\u201d in 2012, a key figure in this regard.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sobesednik.ru/obshchestvo/20191205-femida-na-sluzhbe-u-ofshora|title=\u0424\u0435\u043c\u0438\u0434\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0435 \u0443 \u043e\u0444\u0448\u043e\u0440\u0430|website=sobesednik.ru|language=ru|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n== Hobbies ==\nIn his youth, Mikhail Khabarov had involvement in athletics, water and mountain skiing, but he's most notable for his career as an amateur poker player. His best result was 13th place in the No Limit Hold'em Event #4 in the [[European Poker Tour|EPT]] National in Sochi for a prize of US$7,963. He has a total of  US$ 16,573 career earnings.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pokernews.com/poker-players/mikhail-khabarov/|title=Mikhail Khabarov {{!}} Poker Players {{!}} PokerNews|publisher=www.pokernews.com|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldpokertour.com/player/mikhail-khabarov/|title=Mikhail Khabarov {{!}} World Poker Tour|lang=en-US|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.globalpokerindex.com/poker-players/mikhail-khabarov-975871/|title=Mikhail Khabarov {{!}} KZJ574 {{!}} Russia {{!}} The Official Global Poker Index \u2013 GPI Rankings|website=www.globalpokerindex.com|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n<!--- See [[Wikipedia:Footnotes]] on how to create references using <ref></ref> tags which will then appear here automatically -->\n{{Reflist}}\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Russian bankers]]\n[[Category:Russian poker players]]\n[[Category:Russian chief executives]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Russian businessman}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Mikhail Kharabov\n| birth_date         = March 12, 1971\n| birth_place        = [[Zlatoust]], [[Chelyabinsk]], [[URSS]]\n| nationality        = {{flagicon|RUS}} Russian\n| occupation         = Businessman, Manager\n}}\n'''Mikhail Valentinovich Khabarov''' (born in March 12, 1971, in [[Zlatoust]], [[Chelyabinsk]], [[Soviet Union|USSR]]) is a [[Russia|Russian]] businessman and manager. He is the current board president, and [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] of National Bank TRUST<ref name=\"trust\">{{cite web|url=https://www.trust.ru/upload/documents/about/leaders/government_body_02122019.pdf|title=\u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0431\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430 \u0422\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0442|website=Trust|accessdate=2019-12-02}}</ref>, an institution part of the [[Central Bank of Russia]]'s activities to improve the national banking system.\n\n== Biography ==\n\n=== Early life ===\nMikhail Khabarov was born in Zlatoust, Chelyabinsk, USSR, in a family of [[Metallurgy|metallurgists]]. His parents wanted that his son continued the family's business, but Khaborov didn't settle as the material life of his parents didn't impress him. In his first opportunity, he left his hometown for [[Moscow]].<ref name=\"forbes\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.ru/forbes/issue/2007-03/12083-ohotnik-za-millionerami|title=\u041e\u0445\u043e\u0442\u043d\u0438\u043a \u0437\u0430 \u043c\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043c\u0438|website=Forbes|accessdate=2020-02-26}}</ref>\n\n=== Education ===\nMikhail Khabarov joined the Moscow Institute of Steel and Alloys State Technological University (currently known as [[National University of Science and Technology MISiS (Russia)|National University of Science and Technology MISiS]]). He graduated in 1993 in Automation of Technological Processes and Metallurgical Production.<ref name=\"forbes\" /><ref name=\"finparty\">{{cite web|url=https://finparty.ru/personal/mikhail-khabarov/|title=\u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432|website=Finparty|accessdate=2020-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/1227444|title=8 \u043e\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430|date=2009-09-07|publisher=www.kommersant.ru|lang=ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref> In 1994, he concluded his studies in the Higher Commercial School, under the Russian Federation's [[Ministry of Foreign Economic Relations (Soviet Union)|Ministry of Foreign Economic Relations]]. In 2001, he received his MBA from [[Pepperdine University]]  ([[California]], [[United States|USA]]).<ref name=\"finparty\" /> Speculation in Russia suggested that the true motive of his departure from Russia to USA in the Fall of 1998, was a criminal prosecution from various of the most important managers of the financial and industrial group [[Magnitogorsk Iron and Steel Works]]. Khabarov was accused of [[embezzlement]] of a 30% stake in Magnitogorsk Iron and Steel Works, and asset withdrawal.<ref name=\"skelet\">{{Cite web|url=https://finance.rambler.ru/other/43424867-skelet-v-shkafu-seo-trasta-mihaila-habarova/|title=\u0421\u043a\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0442 \u0432 \u0448\u043a\u0430\u0444\u0443 \u0421\u0415\u041e \u00ab\u0422\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0430\u00bb \u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430|publisher=\u0420\u0430\u043c\u0431\u043b\u0435\u0440/\u0444\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043d\u0441\u044b|lang=ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nMikhael Khabarov started his career as a window cleaner, and worked as an ice cream salesman.<ref name=\"snob\">{{cite web|url=https://snob.ru/profile/5282|title=\u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432|website=\u0421\u043d\u043e\u0431|accessdate=2020-02-26}}</ref> In 1993-1994, he was employed at the Department of Automation in the Ministry of Metallurgy of Russian Federadion. In an interview some years later, Khabarov recalled that, when applying for the job, the interviewer made the following note on his resume: \u201cHe has zero knowledge in finance, but he understands metallurgy,\u201d and that he was then appointed on probation in the bank\u2019s corporate finance department<ref name=\"snob\" /> \n\n=== Inkombank and Magnitogorsk Steel ===\nIn 1994, he was hired by [[Inkombank]] as manager-in-chief. In 1996, Khabarov moved to the office of Deputy Director of Economy, Finance, and Strategical Development in the financial and industrial group Magnitogorsk Steel, that along with Inkombank and FIG, held Magnitogorsk Iron and Steel Works (MMK).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/182026|title=Trans World \u0438 \u0418\u043d\u043a\u043e\u043c\u0431\u0430\u043d\u043a \u043d\u0430 \u041c\u0430\u0433\u043d\u0438\u0442\u043a\u0435|date=1997-08-05|publisher=www.kommersant.ru|lang=ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref> Khabarov worked in the team under Rashit Sharipov, Chairman of the Board of Directors of the Magnitogorsk Iron and Steel works. In the same year, e and his wife and son moved to the United States, and moved back to Russia after the statute of limitations for the criminal cases related to the Magnitogorsk Iron and Steel Works had expired.<ref name=\"skelet\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vekdaily.com/economy/skeleton-in-the-closet-of-trust-bank-ceo-mikhail-khabarov|title=Skeleton in the Closet of Trust Bank CEO Mikhail Khabarov|website=Vekdaily.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n=== ROSNO Asset Management Alliance ===\nBack to Russia, Mikhail Khabarov was hired by the Finance Director of the Insurance Company [[ROSNO]]. In 2004, Khabarov created and presided over ROSNO Asset Management Alliance. According to Forbes, in the exact period, the co-owner of [[Alfa Group|Alfa Capital]]<ref name=\"forbes\" />, [[Mikhail Fridman]] was looking for a CEO. In May 2006, Khabarov left ROSNO with a group of specialists to Alfa Capital.<ref name=\"famp\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.ru/amp/376323/|title=\u0421\u043f\u0435\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0441\u0442 \u043f\u043e \u043f\u043b\u043e\u0445\u0438\u043c \u0434\u043e\u043b\u0433\u0430\u043c. CEO \u0431\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430 \u00ab\u0422\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0442\u00bb \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b \u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432 {{!}} Forbes.ru|publisher=www.forbes.ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref>\n\n=== Alfa Group ===\nIn October 2010, he became president of the investments company A1 ([[Alfa Group]]'s division of investments), while remaining Chairman of the Board of Directors at Alfa Capital. At the same time, he joined Supervisory Board of Alfa Group.<ref name=\"finparty\" /> Under Khabarov, A1 managed the Alfa Distressed Assets Fund (ADA), which redeemed troubled collateral assets from Alfa Group, and made them operational again before selling them on. In this process, nearly US$2 billions of toxic assets were brought under the control of A1.<ref name=\"famp\" /> \n\nKhabarov conducted A1 to become one of the most aggressive players in the market of hostile takeovers and applying all sorts of raider tools from quasi-legal methods to more primitive forms of exerting pressure, including initiating criminal cases against intractable opponents.<ref>http://www.ng.ru/economics/2020-01-30/100_trast300120.html</ref> Indeed, media reported on some of the most controversial cases in which A1 was involved, including the liquidation of the budget airline [[Avianova (Russia)|Avianova]], the interception of liquid assets of Russia\u2019s largest ceramic tile producer Stroyfarfor, the illegal takeover and its alleged manipulation of US and EU sanctions against defense enterprises [[Rostec]] and [[Uralvagonzavod]], among others.<ref name=\"versia\">{{Cite web|url=https://versia.ru/ploximi-dolgami-v-gosbanke-trast-zanimaetsya-byvshij-direktor-a1-mixail-xabarov|title=\u041f\u043b\u043e\u0445\u0438\u043c\u0438 \u0434\u043e\u043b\u0433\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u0432 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0431\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0435 \u00ab\u0422\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0442\u00bb \u0437\u0430\u043d\u0438\u043c\u0430\u0435\u0442\u0441\u044f \u0431\u044b\u0432\u0448\u0438\u0439 \u0434\u0438\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u04101 \u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432|publisher=versia.ru|lang=ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref>  \n\nKhabarov's management of A1 lasted until December 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vedomosti.ru/newspaper/articles/2015/02/26/habarov-vzyalsya-za-furi|title=\u0411\u044b\u0432\u0448\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u04101 \u0437\u0430\u0439\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0441\u044f \u0444\u0443\u0440\u0430\u043c\u0438|publisher=\u0412\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438|lang=ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref> By the time Mikhail Khabarov was named for the National Trust Bank, in 2019, media called Khabarov \"something between a racketeer and a collector\".<ref name=\"versia\" /> Since 2014, Khabarov has been co-owner and president of the logistics company Delovie Linii.<ref name=\"snob\" /> \n\n=== National Bank TRUST ===\nIn May 2019, he was named Prime First Deputy President-Chairman of the Management Board and Chief Executive Officer of the National Bank TRUST Non-core Assets.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://worldfinancialreview.com/mikhail-khabarov-of-a1-now-heads-national-bank-trust/|title=Mikhail Khabarov of A1 Now Heads National Bank TRUST|last=|first=|date=|website=World Financial Review|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The bank was created to consolidate bad assets from an extensive clean-up of various financial institutions including [[Otkritie FC Bank|Otkrytie FC]], [[B&N Bank]] , [[Promsvyazbank]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-russia-banks-bad-bank-exclusive-idUSKCN1Q10MH|title=Exclusive: Russia expects to recover far less from 'bad bank' assets - sources|date=2019-02-12|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-03-12|language=en}}</ref>. Khabarov is responsible for the issues related to money charges: administration and sales of assets, and debt collection.<ref name=\"famp\" /> The amount of problematic assets consolidated in the bank amounts to 450 billion rubles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/3975307|title=\u0413\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u044b\u043c \u0438\u0441\u043f\u043e\u043b\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u043c \u0434\u0438\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043c \u0411\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430 \u043d\u0435\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043e\u0432 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b \u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432|date=2019-05-20|publisher=www.kommersant.ru|lang=ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref> The president of the bank's council, Alexander Sokolov, by the time of Khabarov's appointment, appointed him as \"a professional with good experience in the management of problematic assets\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.finmarket.ru/interview/Default.asp?id=5017787|title=\u0412\u0440\u0435\u043c\u044f \u0432\u0441\u0435\u0433\u0434\u0430 \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u043a\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0430 - \u0433\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0430 \u0431\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430 &quot;\u0422\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0442&quot;|date=2019-06-11|publisher=Finmarket.ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref> At the same time, media observed that Khabarov was recruiting former employees from A1, with dubious reputations to work with National Bank TRUST.<ref name=\"versia\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pravda.ru/society/1467649-Mikhail_Khabarov/|title=\u041c\u0435\u0442\u043e\u0434\u044b \u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0431\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0437\u0430\u043c\u0433\u043b\u0430\u0432\u044b \u0431\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430 \"\u0422\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0442\" \u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430|author=\u041f\u0435\u0442\u0440 \u0414\u0435\u0440\u044f\u0431\u0438\u043d|date=2020-01-17|publisher=\u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0434\u0430.\u0420\u0443|lang=ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://oneworldherald.com/2020/01/05/national-bank-trust-executive-director-mikhail-khabarov-goes-big/|title=National bank Trust executive director Mikhail Khabarov goes big|last=heraldadmin|date=2020-01-05|website=OneWorldHerald.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n== Conflict within Delovie Linii ==\nIn 2015, Khabarov became co-owner of one of the largest logistics companies in Russia - Delovie Linii. In August 2017, Khabarov had a conflict with other co-owner Alexander Bogatikov. In September 2019, Solarstones Limited, a company from [[Seychelles]], controlled by Khabarov, installed a lawsuit of US$ 25 million against Bogatikov and his company DL Management Limited, in the [[London Court of International Arbitration]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.ru/biznes/386747-sud-zapretil-vladelcam-delovyh-liniy-prodavat-svoi-aktivy|title=\u0421\u0443\u0434 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043b \u0432\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0446\u0430\u043c \u00ab\u0414\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445 \u043b\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0439\u00bb \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0438 \u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u044b {{!}} \u0411\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441|date=2019-11-05|publisher=Forbes.ru|lang=en-US|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref> Following a lawsuit filed by Solarstones Limited, the [[Primorsky District, Arkhangelsk Oblast|Primorsky]] District Court of [[Saint Petersburg|St. Petersburg]] prohibited any transactions for eight companies included in the Delovie Linii group, and inspectorate No. 15 of the Federal Tax Service for St. Petersburg registered such transactions as subjects of injunctive relief on 18 October 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sobesednik.ru/obshchestvo/20191205-femida-na-sluzhbe-u-ofshora|title=\u0424\u0435\u043c\u0438\u0434\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0435 \u0443 \u043e\u0444\u0448\u043e\u0440\u0430|publisher=sobesednik.ru|lang=ru|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.ru/biznes/386747-sud-zapretil-vladelcam-delovyh-liniy-prodavat-svoi-aktivy|title=\u0421\u0443\u0434 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043b \u0432\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0446\u0430\u043c \u00ab\u0414\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445 \u043b\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0439\u00bb \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0438 \u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u044b {{!}} \u0411\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441|date=2019-11-05|website=Forbes.ru|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\nAccording to media reports, these injunctions represent the next stage of a raid on the Delovie Linii, with judge Natalya Karpenkova, who was disciplined for \u201cgross and systematic violation of the procedural legislation\u201d in 2012, a key figure in this regard.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sobesednik.ru/obshchestvo/20191205-femida-na-sluzhbe-u-ofshora|title=\u0424\u0435\u043c\u0438\u0434\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0435 \u0443 \u043e\u0444\u0448\u043e\u0440\u0430|website=sobesednik.ru|language=ru|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n== Hobbies ==\nIn his youth, Mikhail Khabarov had involvement in athletics, water and mountain skiing, but he's most notable for his career as an amateur poker player. His best result was 13th place in the No Limit Hold'em Event #4 in the [[European Poker Tour|EPT]] National in Sochi for a prize of US$7,963. He has a total of  US$ 16,573 career earnings.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pokernews.com/poker-players/mikhail-khabarov/|title=Mikhail Khabarov {{!}} Poker Players {{!}} PokerNews|publisher=www.pokernews.com|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldpokertour.com/player/mikhail-khabarov/|title=Mikhail Khabarov {{!}} World Poker Tour|lang=en-US|accessdate=2020-03-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.globalpokerindex.com/poker-players/mikhail-khabarov-975871/|title=Mikhail Khabarov {{!}} KZJ574 {{!}} Russia {{!}} The Official Global Poker Index \u2013 GPI Rankings|website=www.globalpokerindex.com|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n<!--- See [[Wikipedia:Footnotes]] on how to create references using <ref></ref> tags which will then appear here automatically -->\n{{Reflist}}\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Russian bankers]]\n[[Category:Russian poker players]]\n[[Category:Russian chief executives]]\n", "name_user": "Cnwilliams", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguated:URSS\u2192USSR", "url_pag